cs.CR, cs.HC, cs.SY, cs.IR, cs.NI 

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category as it presents a system for securely pairing wearable devices by generating a shared secret key. It also discusses the robustness of the system against different types of attacks. 

It could also belong to the cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) sub-category as it involves wearable devices and their interaction with the human body. 

The cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category is also a possibility as the paper discusses the design and implementation of a system for generating secret keys. 

The cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category is a possibility as the paper discusses the extraction of useful entropy from noisy piezo measurements. 

Finally, the cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-category is a possibility as the paper discusses the potential power saving opportunity arising from the use of energy-efficient piezo sensors for detecting heartbeat intervals.
